-- Bayern Wins Heynckes’s Final League Game as Coach
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-05-18T16:40:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-18/bayern-wins-heynckes-s-final-league-game-as-coach-correct-.html
(Corrects to final league game in headline, first
paragraph.)  Bayern Munich  came from behind to
beat Moenchengladbach 4-3 in Jupp Heynckes’s final Bundesliga
game as coach of the German soccer champion.  Franck Ribery scored twice for Bayern, which trailed 3-1
after 10 minutes. Heynckes will retire after the German Cup
final on June 1 and will be replaced by former Barcelona coach
Pep Guardiola.  Schalke beat Freiburg 2-1 to finish in fourth place and
join Bayern, Borussia Dortmund and Bayer Leverkusen in next
season’s  Champions League . Bayern and Dortmund meet in this
season’s Champions League final May 25.  Fortuna Duesseldorf lost 3-0 to Hannover and joins last-place Greuther Fuerth in being relegated to Bundesliga 2 next
season.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  